Bitcoin tumbles as Putin orders military into Eastern Ukraine Overnight, Russian President Vladimir Putin authorised what he called a special military operation in eastern Ukraine but Ukraine’s Foreign Minister Dmytro Kuleba said on Twitter that Russia had launched a “full-scale invasion”. Read:
Biden says US will impose ‘further consequences’ on Russia According to Statistics South Africa South Africa’s annual producer price inflation eased to 10.1% in January 2022 from 10.8% in December 2021, but rose 0.2% month-on-month. Economists polled by Reuters had predicted PPI would ease to 10.5% from 10.8% in December. The main contributors were coke, petroleum, chemical, rubber and plastic products (up 21.5% year-on-year); metals, machinery, equipment and computing equipment (up 12.1%); and food products, beverages and tobacco products (up 6.1% year-on-year).